to approximate patient-speciÔ¨Åc in vivo conditions. Other main elements are the inclusion of non-Newtonian Ô¨Çuid
corrections and the proper capturing of the interaction between the Ô¨Çow and the aneurysm structure. In all these
aspects, attention should be given to the computational robustness of predictions, focusing on the relation between the
general topology of Ô¨Çow structures and the shear stress characteristics.
